transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Yeah, this is John Statura.

Speaker 1: Hello?

Speaker 2: Yes, let me pull your prescription.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay.

Speaker 2: Okay, Mr. John Statura, how can I help you, sir?

Speaker 1: I want to cancel my prescription.

Speaker 2: I see that you just placed an order today, but I think that you placed—

Speaker 1: I don't know if you mean to do that, but I see an order, two orders—

Speaker 2: actually, a double order, one for 50 milligrams, one for 25 milligrams.

Speaker 1: You know, I must have hit something wrong—

Speaker 2: because I automatically got billed through my PayPal for the 50—

Speaker 1: and that's why I'm calling.

Speaker 2: I thought this was out.

Speaker 1: I can cancel that, yeah.

Speaker 2: I mean, if you want whatever you want, 25 or 50, I can cancel one of them.

Speaker 1: Oh, I want them both canceled.

Speaker 2: Oh, okay.

Speaker 1: Okay, I canceled both orders, sir.

Speaker 2: Great.

Speaker 1: Now, will that go automatically back on my PayPal account?

Speaker 2: Because I've already been charged.

Speaker 1: Yeah, that should go back, because we refunded the money.

Speaker 2: Now it's, you know, the bank to do the job.

Speaker 1: But I refunded you, I think it was 163.95—

Speaker 2: and it was another one for 63.95 order, yeah.

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: Okay, and then if I'm going to keep this, you know—

Speaker 1: Is my account still valid if I want to order something in the future?

Speaker 2: Yes, if you don't want anything at the moment—

Speaker 1: I can advise the pharmacy to pause, and you just reorder in the future.

Speaker 2: They can pause you up to half a year, and you can order before—

Speaker 1: 90 days, whatever you want to do.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, let's do that.

Speaker 1: Let's keep the order or keep my information, but I'll call when I want more.

Speaker 2: Okay, so I'm going to have the pharmacy pausing you.

Speaker 1: They pause up to half a year, so you don't get monthly or stuff like that—

Speaker 2: you can reorder.

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: All right, so you're all set, okay?

Speaker 2: All right, thanks a lot.

Speaker 1: You're welcome.

Speaker 2: You have a good one.

Speaker 1: All right, bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
